

-static is keyword in java
-static means fix (only one copy is created)
-In Java, static means something belongs to the class, not to the object.
-there are three use of static 
  1) static varible
  2) static method
  3) static block

1) static varible
 - only one copy is created.
 - use for auto increment.

* syntax--> static datatype varible;
* Example-->static int a;

2) static method(call without object)
 -Static method can be called using the class name.
 -It cannot access non-static (normal) variables directly.

 * syntax--> static returntype methodname(arg list)
             {
              //code
             }
 * Example-->

      class MyClass {
    static void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello!");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MyClass.greet();  // No object needed
    }
}
